-zLLw8wjQsIHrQs3h1s4aGNdXI1ktyfV73f3zHnu9-fYpwIhS_-AHS9uxca2_MDTd7lI6x3iNxY9MPWILcfxuZpHEFqI_fJ3_uWLOfrdwfBEVZkH7GwzBle5vfVpSu67Tw5gkahvzzd9tV7-FU5CYIhutKMtEkHn1RwqSHVCo7iRkaInQxoUzCBjhtuyu3E3i6PTv4atJiMrDKu6xx6bycoNIbmthwBEzuUyqXspFnZb9v6Xx7VV6XFdC3F0-5ecDj5L89BQB9NH3vm4ordFUzyg6DxhbLYcbT6ol2CxfkbPg_mn0v2avpN0UX4STliBZ4teRxsVscgR7eC7FBjIyZUR_XKZ7gc_NY6Sr5Np4mMDQ8VEXL2LKQJSIkX2I5w1TMGb9IPZkOuKph4QbXHEFLzBMqzlFZHnp9778LG9Nh8o9z1snr0S8J0ZcxU5SXAcfE8V_jRBz6c2d1nNYxta1BY-I8coUc6yczQHfjgv1cercj7_fA513Viv76DHV4uA0Pb4MZqrr68tV3VXDHu2-wQMQLNES4AB7H6UK0RegYiQSeVkqnBl1W8gqkx2I56SPaK4U07oygeyVkwdWebrskHjSNC5DfLRcBxGP-8dfJYmNZ_HdbhWUJtZj1f3-91AKOXO6_dW4nw8CaufL7SGjEEaowVaWequA9dMiTUNhn6WtCU7KbA5srEaMj0RDaRc8s5xQ_H11EBj4BaslNyFhZt_bYthKwMNFOFgIndeaO22UToDuns2lvDAAQfLcgiS0HXTlMw8MGWZ9w-0_GxyHssB5toXvLU_wrosZ1fJhU-Ih7pigyT6itQYAV7djwUpyXjkZJz3mGQ55deU9kZblF3UN4Y6GcKXc0eBusI8vrh3n3LPcoL5510sFyQM5uYGsqotnZ_7yGFFAZhgSBrcN-4LeOa6HcudVXz_M1lXy5r-EkQ9TsKksBnyAKIAXjyc1lia88GZBWXl6PfVIpiHut0AAyGPJk6lDmhNNaMNS6A20ncFU4GeL5_cc2NQFRjDeEXbnKq8ewxdLBxxp1Q=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Reviewing constructor access**\\n\\nI’m figuring out the access level for the default constructor in a public class. It seems the default constructor has the same accessibility as the class itself, which is public. So I can instantiate a new `ContextSelectorStaticBinder` without introducing singleton or key side effects. I plan to call init with a new object, keeping it free of global state. It looks like public API constructors are indeed implicit. I'll have to check the behavior of `DefaultContextSelector`, especially regarding null names. That could be a potential issue.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_ZRNDal3N0Wx7cq9RI54KQ86o|fc_0aee69693b29e43d0169f00e25e88081938dec5fc1f875842a", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/1.5.30/src/test/java/org/graalvm/logback/ContextSelectorStaticBinderTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org.graalvm.logback;\n\nimport ch.qos.logback.classic.ClassicConstants;\nimport ch.qos.logback.classic.LoggerContext;\nimport ch.qos.logback.classic.selector.ContextSelector;\nimport ch.qos.logback.classic.selector.DefaultContextSelector;\nimport ch.qos.logback.classic.util.ContextSelectorStaticBinder;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class ContextSelectorStaticBinderTest {\n\n  @Test\n  void initializesConfiguredContextSelectorByClassName() throws Exception {\n    String previousContextSelector = System.getProperty(ClassicConstants.LOGBACK_CONTEXT_SELECTOR);\n    LoggerContext loggerContext = new LoggerContext();\n    loggerContext.setName(\"context-selector-static-binder-test\");\n\n    try {\n      System.setProperty(ClassicConstants.LOGBACK_CONTEXT_SELECTOR, DefaultContextSelector.class.getName());\n\n      ContextSelectorStaticBinder binder = new ContextSelectorStaticBinder();\n      binder.init(loggerContext, ContextSelectorStaticBinderTest.class);\n\n      ContextSelector contextSelector = binder.getContextSelector();\n      assertThat(contextSelector).isInstanceOf(DefaultContextSelector.class);\n      assertThat(contextSelector.getDefaultLoggerContext()).isSameAs(loggerContext);\n      assertThat(contextSelector.getLoggerContext(loggerContext.getName())).isSameAs(loggerContext);\n    } finally {\n      restoreContextSelectorProperty(previousContextSelector);\n      loggerContext.stop();\n    }\n  }\n\n  private static void restoreContextSelectorProperty(String previousContextSelector) {\n    if (previousContextSelector == null) {\n      System.clearProperty(ClassicConstants.LOGBACK_CONTEXT_SELECTOR);\n    } else {\n      System.setProperty(ClassicConstants.LOGBACK_CONTEXT_SELECTOR, previousContextSelector);\n    }\n  }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1089, "output": 1998, "cacheRead": 24576, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27663, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777339921056, "responseId": "resp_0aee69693b29e43d0169f00e118de48193a51f608c1a597420"}}
